edu.rit.pj2.tuple

Class ObjectArrayTuple<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.pj2.Tuple
      • edu.rit.pj2.tuple.ObjectArrayTuple<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Content data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable, Cloneable

    public class ObjectArrayTuple<T>
extends Tuple
    Class ObjectArrayTuple provides a Tuple that contains an array of objects. The objects must be streamable or serializable.

    • Method Detail

      • matchContent

        public boolean matchContent(Tuple target)
        Determine if the given target tuple's content matches this template's content. The target tuple is assumed to be an instance of this template's matching class or a subclass thereof.

        The ObjectTuple class's matchContent() method returns true if any of the following are true:

        • This template tuple's item array is null.
        • The target tuple's item array is null.
        • The element type of the target tuple's item array is the same as (or a subclass of) the element type of this template tuple's item array.
        Overrides:
        matchContent in class Tuple
        Parameters:
        target - Target tuple.
        Returns:
        True if the target tuple's content matches this template tuple's content, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if target is null.
